This program mimics the system call 'ls'. Flags include '-a' or '-r'.

Accepted Command Line Arguments:
./a.out
./a.out -a
./a.out directoryNameHere
./a.out directoryNameHere -a
./a.out directoryNameHere -r
./a.out -r

Dependencies:
Download apue.3e from the following site: http://www.apuebook.com/code3e.html

Compilation example:
gcc -I./apue.3e/include -L./apue.3e/lib  newLs.c -lapue

Run example:
./a.out
